<br>
Manuverability!<br>
<br>
Running through crowded hallways while being chased by big scary things.<br>
<br>
Ability to squeeze between bars in some &quot;jails&quot;.<br>
<br>
Ease of picking your way through a crowded raid to hand a stack of food or a damage bracer to a needy guildmate.<br>
<br>
Running up between melees in large group situations to do toe-to-toe Bolt shots (not necessary against GIANT and Largish mobs, but very helpful with smaller mobs).<br>
<br>
Group of fat ass ogre's have ya pinned to a wall?  Gnomes are the MASTERS of escaping such places.  Rare is the tight spot that a gnome cannot squeeze through without ducking or jumping.<br>
<br>
Lady's DIG gnomes! (okay, not really a manuverabilty issue, but valid nonetheless)<br>
<br>
<br>
Really, the only problem with choosing a gnome is that there are one or two areas in the game that force you to JUMP where others can just walk.  Turnabout is fair play though, as there are INFINATELY more areas where we can simply walk through where they have to crouch, or for the fat asses, ask for a shrink.<br>
<br>
<br>
THE GNOME REVOLUTION HAS BEGUN!  THE REVOLUTION WILL NOT BE TELEVISED!<br>
